    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The websocket connection still being valid is fine because logging out doesn't invalidate the credentials used to authenticate the websocket. It's not _revoking_ the cookie, it's just clearing it from the browser's memory. If we had a 'revoke cookie' action, then it would make sense to forcibly close the websockets.\n"
